30:33.832 --> 30:35.166
(sniffs) Dude...

30:35.184 --> 30:37.001
Dude, yourself.

30:37.019 --> 30:39.170
What the hell is this?

30:39.188 --> 30:41.222
(grunts)

30:41.273 --> 30:43.558
Uh, it's from my sociology prof.

30:43.609 --> 30:45.360
Guess I missed another test.
No biggie.

30:45.394 --> 30:47.145
Crap, what time is it?

30:47.179 --> 30:48.346
I'm late to play Frolf
with that Cromley guy.

30:48.364 --> 30:51.366
Dude, it is a biggie.
It's a very biggie.

30:51.400 --> 30:53.401
Isn't that class one of your
requirements for your teaching major?

30:53.452 --> 30:55.036
Don't worry,
I'm gonna pass that class.

30:55.070 --> 30:56.538
The... the final's worth,
like, 60% of the grade.

30:56.572 --> 30:57.739
I'll just cram and ace it.

30:57.790 --> 30:58.790
Is that your dream?

30:58.824 --> 30:59.857
To barely skate through school

30:59.875 --> 31:01.526
and become a mediocre teacher?

31:01.560 --> 31:03.878
Wait, since when do you care
about school so much, man?

31:03.913 --> 31:05.213
You're not even in school.
Dude.

31:05.247 --> 31:06.697
This isn't high school anymore.

31:06.715 --> 31:08.049
It's not just about potential.

31:08.083 --> 31:10.034
This is the real casaba.

31:10.052 --> 31:11.085
So you're a crappy
high school student.

31:11.136 --> 31:12.220
Who cares?

31:12.254 --> 31:13.471
But if you're a crappy teacher,

31:13.505 --> 31:14.756
that means something.

31:14.807 --> 31:16.507
(sighs)

31:16.541 --> 31:18.092
Look.

31:18.143 --> 31:19.344
This has been awesome.

31:19.378 --> 31:21.045
I'm having the time of my life.

31:21.063 --> 31:22.597
And doing it with my best bud

31:22.648 --> 31:24.215
is a dream come true.

31:24.233 --> 31:26.050
But last night, I was
in bed with three chicks,

31:26.068 --> 31:27.402
and I was thinking,
"What is this all about

31:27.436 --> 31:28.553
for you, Puckerman?"

31:28.587 --> 31:30.889
So, what'd you come up with?

31:30.923 --> 31:32.440
I want to show all of 'em.

31:32.491 --> 31:35.276
Everyone who ever
crossed the street

31:35.327 --> 31:36.411
when I came down the sidewalk

31:36.445 --> 31:38.229
or didn't call on me in class

31:38.247 --> 31:39.664
'cause they just assumed
I'd fart my answer,

31:39.698 --> 31:41.950
or told me I'd be
pumping gas someday

31:42.001 --> 31:44.235
that we are worth something.

31:44.253 --> 31:46.788
That we are more
than they say we are.

31:46.839 --> 31:48.289
(sighs)

31:48.340 --> 31:50.425
I'm not saying we
need to stop having

31:50.459 --> 31:52.377
a good time,
but partying this hard,

31:52.411 --> 31:54.078
skipping out on tests,

31:54.096 --> 31:56.247
that's their vision
of who we are.

31:56.265 --> 31:57.915
Doesn't have to be ours.

31:57.933 --> 32:00.602
So what are you gonna do,
like, enroll here now?

32:00.636 --> 32:02.103
I still think school's
for suckers,

32:02.137 --> 32:03.805
but I'm gonna stay here
and write my screenplay

32:03.856 --> 32:05.089
and be on your ass

32:05.107 --> 32:07.141
24-7 to make sure
that you become

32:07.192 --> 32:08.943
the best teacher
that you can be.

32:08.978 --> 32:10.594
We've always known
we were special.

32:10.613 --> 32:12.864
This is our chance to prove it.

32:14.867 --> 32:16.284
Yeah.

32:21.123 --> 32:23.207
(warbles) Ew.

32:23.242 --> 32:24.442
(laughs) Get to work.

32:24.460 --> 32:25.960
I'll grab the iron and make us

32:25.995 --> 32:27.745
some grilled cheeses.

32:27.779 --> 32:29.780
(groans)

32:35.120 --> 32:37.639
(school bell rings)

32:37.673 --> 32:38.973
Mm.

32:39.008 --> 32:40.892
You wanted to see us, Coach?
Yes.

32:40.926 --> 32:42.644
Come on in and have a seat.

32:42.678 --> 32:44.395
It is my understanding

32:44.430 --> 32:46.297
that I have inherited you

32:46.315 --> 32:49.067
as co-captains
of the Cheerios!

32:49.101 --> 32:50.968
And by looking at the
two of you right now,

32:50.986 --> 32:54.072
that makes me
extremely suspicious.

32:54.106 --> 32:55.807
Suspicious? Why?

32:55.874 --> 32:57.308
Oh, I understand why.

32:57.326 --> 32:58.993
Coach Sylvester's
daughter Robin is here.

32:59.028 --> 33:00.028
Sue Sylvester

33:00.079 --> 33:02.330
is as old as the hills,

33:02.364 --> 33:05.166
so when she gave birth
to her fully grown,

33:05.200 --> 33:08.202
16-year-old baby with
Down syndrome, it was

33:08.253 --> 33:09.820
a miracle, and she wanted

33:09.838 --> 33:12.807
to bring her to school every day
and show her off.

33:12.841 --> 33:14.926
You're the one that makes
me suspicious,

33:14.960 --> 33:16.160
Fruity Fonzie.

33:16.178 --> 33:17.845
You ain't never done
a cheerleading routine

33:17.880 --> 33:19.497
in your life,

33:19.515 --> 33:21.499
but somehow you get.

33:21.517 --> 33:23.134
Sue Sylvester to make you

33:23.168 --> 33:24.835
co-captain of the Cheerios!,

33:24.853 --> 33:27.671
and then, three weeks later,
out of nowhere,

33:27.690 --> 33:29.724
Sue Sylvester gets fired.

33:29.775 --> 33:30.942
That makes me

33:30.976 --> 33:32.543
real suspicious.

33:32.578 --> 33:35.730
That makes me think
that you used your handsome

33:35.781 --> 33:38.516
fruity voodoo powers
and put a hex on her

33:38.534 --> 33:41.619
that caused her to bring a gun
to school for no reason

33:41.653 --> 33:44.539
and get real clumsy
so she drops it twice

33:44.573 --> 33:46.207
and it goes off both times.

33:46.241 --> 33:47.692
That sounds like

33:47.726 --> 33:50.661
some dark-sided, fruity
voodoo stuff to me.

33:50.695 --> 33:52.380
But that didn't really happen!

33:52.414 --> 33:54.031
Blaine had nothing
to do with it!

33:54.049 --> 33:55.583
How do you know?
Were you there?

33:55.634 --> 33:57.034
No.

33:57.052 --> 33:58.669
Exactly.
So here's

33:58.703 --> 34:00.221
the deal... if you
want to stay

34:00.255 --> 34:02.706
on board as co-captain
of the Cheerios!,

34:02.725 --> 34:06.210
you're gonna have to take
a blood oath and loyalty pledge.

34:06.228 --> 34:08.429
What? A blood oath?

34:08.480 --> 34:09.647
Is-is that even safe?

34:09.681 --> 34:10.715
Probably not.

34:10.748 --> 34:11.949
So we'll just take the oath.

34:11.984 --> 34:13.217
Repeat after me.

34:13.252 --> 34:16.571
I, Fruity Fonzie
and adult baby Robin...

34:16.605 --> 34:21.159
BOTH: I, Fruity Fonzie
and adult baby Robin...

34:21.193 --> 34:24.395
...do solemnly swear... BOTH:.
..do solemnly swear...

34:24.429 --> 34:29.117
...to <i>never</i> put a hex
on Coach Roz Washington.

34:29.168 --> 34:30.900
To <i>never</i> To <i>never</i>

34:30.918 --> 34:34.172
hex on Coach Roz Washington. To...
on Coach Roz Washington.

34:34.206 --> 34:37.507
Causing her to bring a gun to
school so she gets real clumsy

34:37.543 --> 34:40.578
and drops it and it goes off
twice in a row.

34:40.596 --> 34:42.179
BOTH: Causing her to
bring a gun to school

34:42.214 --> 34:44.047
so she gets real clumsy
and drops it

34:44.081 --> 34:46.067
so it goes off twice in a row.

34:46.101 --> 34:47.418
So help me God.

34:47.436 --> 34:48.753
BOTH:
So help me God.

34:48.786 --> 34:49.937
You are free to go.

34:53.275 --> 34:54.475
(bell ringing)

34:55.527 --> 34:57.278
Becky, wait up.

34:57.312 --> 34:59.781
Hurry up, I'm gonna be
late for calculus.

34:59.815 --> 35:03.401
Becky, um, you were acting
particularly strange

35:03.435 --> 35:05.319
in there just now.

35:05.370 --> 35:06.654
Do you know something I don't

35:06.705 --> 35:08.122
about what happened
with Coach Sue?

35:08.157 --> 35:11.108
Mind your own gay business,
gay Blaine.

35:11.126 --> 35:13.411
I don't know anything!

35:13.445 --> 35:15.079
(groans)

35:16.448 --> 35:18.049
(groans)

35:33.849 --> 35:35.900
(distance cheering and applause)
(sighs)

35:37.486 --> 35:39.854
(cheering and applause
continues)

35:44.693 --> 35:46.077
(cheering and applause
stops) FINN: Mr. Shue?

35:49.164 --> 35:50.665
You were right.

35:51.667 --> 35:52.984
About what?

35:53.018 --> 35:54.619
(chuckles)

35:54.653 --> 35:55.986
Me.

35:56.004 --> 35:58.656
N-Needing to get my focus back.

35:58.674 --> 36:02.176
So I-I talked to the Dean
of Students about your offer,

36:02.211 --> 36:06.214
and she said she's willing
to give me college credit

36:06.265 --> 36:08.683
for all the time
that I spend here helping out.

36:08.717 --> 36:11.886
Is that your way of saying
apology accepted?

36:11.937 --> 36:14.388
That's my way of saying
I'm willing to come back.

36:14.439 --> 36:15.839
But if I do,

36:15.858 --> 36:19.343
things have got to be different.

36:19.361 --> 36:21.729
No more fetching your coffee

36:21.780 --> 36:25.015
or picking up
your dry cleaning.

36:25.033 --> 36:27.618
I mean, I don't want
to come back to be a gopher.

36:29.071 --> 36:31.022
It's got to be a partnership.

36:31.056 --> 36:32.690
I want to be treated
like an equal.

36:32.708 --> 36:34.492
Like a...

36:34.526 --> 36:36.360
like a teacher.

36:38.397 --> 36:41.582
And then you bring your best
and I bring my best

36:41.633 --> 36:43.551
and we go get another trophy.

36:45.220 --> 36:46.721
That all seems fair.

36:46.755 --> 36:49.373
But I also have a condition.

36:49.408 --> 36:51.893
Let's just move past this.

36:52.928 --> 36:55.713
Right.

37:05.862 --> 37:07.363
(bell ringing)
Looking good, Unique.

37:08.582 --> 37:10.950
(chuckles) You, too, Tina.

37:10.984 --> 37:12.201
Very Jules Verne.

37:13.153 --> 37:15.538
Hey, Blaine. Sam.

37:15.589 --> 37:17.540
I'm Evan. Sam moved to Alaska.

37:17.591 --> 37:20.960
Oh. Well-well, tell him
he's welcome back anytime.

37:23.930 --> 37:25.798
(sighs)

37:30.103 --> 37:33.055
So... just about 20 years ago,

37:33.106 --> 37:35.391
I was sitting right
where you are now.

37:35.442 --> 37:37.309
I was co-captain
of the soccer team

37:37.343 --> 37:39.145
with a forehead full of acne

37:39.179 --> 37:42.031
and a dream of being
the next Vanilla Ice. (Chuckles)

37:42.065 --> 37:43.566
And standing

37:43.617 --> 37:45.651
right here was Mrs. Adler.

37:45.685 --> 37:49.321
She constantly mumbled
to herself and

37:49.355 --> 37:51.257
she stuffed used Kleenex
up her sleeves.

37:51.291 --> 37:54.660
We all were convinced
that she was crazy.

37:54.694 --> 37:56.662
But you know what?

37:56.696 --> 37:58.664
That's why we loved her...

37:58.698 --> 38:00.199
because we were crazy, too.

38:01.301 --> 38:03.752
This is the room
that always felt like home.

38:03.804 --> 38:06.755
Maybe because we knew
Lillian Adler loved music

38:06.807 --> 38:08.841
almost as much as she loved us.

38:10.210 --> 38:12.094
And that's how I feel about you.

38:12.145 --> 38:14.680
Every one of you.

38:14.714 --> 38:16.849
And-and I'm sorry
if I made any of you feel

38:16.883 --> 38:18.851
like you don't have
a voice in this room.

38:18.885 --> 38:20.102
You do.

38:21.488 --> 38:23.439
And I know someone else
who does, too.

38:23.490 --> 38:26.192
(snaps fingers) ARTIE: My man!

38:26.226 --> 38:28.277
(laughter, cheering)

38:28.328 --> 38:31.280
Finn and I are gonna be
working together as a team.

38:31.331 --> 38:32.865
Equal partners.

38:32.899 --> 38:35.234
And we are not gonna
eat, sleep or breathe

38:35.252 --> 38:36.785
until you've blasted
through regionals

38:36.837 --> 38:38.704
and earned your rightful spot
at nationals.

38:38.738 --> 38:40.072
Yes! Yes!
(cheering and applause)

38:42.676 --> 38:43.792
All right, down to business.

38:43.844 --> 38:45.628
Marley, you're up.
Okay.

38:45.679 --> 38:47.630
I haven't quite memorized
"Dream Weaver" yet,

38:47.681 --> 38:49.765
but I think I have "Sweet
Dreams." Didn't I tell you?

38:49.799 --> 38:51.300
Those are out.

38:51.351 --> 38:54.053
I want you to teach us one
of your original songs.

38:54.087 --> 38:56.388
If that's okay.

38:56.422 --> 38:58.607
I'd love that.

